name: Overfull graph
summary:
In graph theory, an overfull graph is a graph whose size is greater than the product of its maximum degree and half of its order floored, i.e. 
  
    
      
        
          |
        
        E
        
          |
        
        >
        Δ
        (
        G
        )
        ⌊
        
          |
        
        V
        
          |
        
        
          /
        
        2
        ⌋
      
    
    {\displaystyle |E|>\Delta (G)\lfloor |V|/2\rfloor }
